      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The lightly raced SHYAMALAN (2) missed the kick last start and struggled to recover in a 1200m Class 1 at Canberra. That run followed a seven-week break so he will tighten up. Steps up to this trip for the first time and the blinkers are removed. This sets up nicely so give him another chance. CALL ME TERRY (4) hasn't been all that far away in two runs since coming back from a break. Out of the winner's list for a long while but he strips fitter and will enjoy this slightly longer journey. ICONIQUE (7) resumes. Will be better for this hit-out but with just 55kgs under today's scale he can sneak into the numbers. CHECK YOUR SIX (5) has been disappointing this prep but a handful of gear changes may be effective. MORE VOLTAGE (8) drops back from provincial company and can improve on some ordinary efforts of late.",
